    <text>
    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Dec 19<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 74.</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>It is extremely kind of you to have thought of sending me your work on the Methods of Ethics.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> Before long I hope to find time to read it, for it is subject which interests me deeply.</p>
<p>With very sincere thanks | Yours faithfully | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">There is a copy of Sidgwick’s <hi rend="italic">Methods of ethics</hi> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7180.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Sidgwick 1874</ref>) in the Darwin Library–Down.</note>
        </div>        
            
